9T11:57:10.533Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-09T11:57:10.533Z","version":1},{"id":"mlf4aakl6smdiub0qg","type":"text","x":320,"y":2990,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","text":"MigrationTarget (created)\n\nmigration_id:    ← rule.migration_id\nrepo:            ← project.gitUrl\npath_in_repo:    ← falcon.relativePath\nlogical_name:    ← project.name\nstatus:          ← NOT_STARTED\nframework:       ← falcon.framework\nownership_tag:   ← DevEx(artifactId)\nfocus:           ← violations[].title\nfile_paths:      ← optional (from rule)","fontSize":14,"fontFamily":"5","createdAt":"2026-02-09T11:57:10.533Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-09T11:57:10.533Z","version":1},{"id":"mlf4aaklqgk54yjlsw","type":"rectangle","x":780,"y":2980,"width":490,"height":300,"backgroundColor":"#fff9db","strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","createdAt":"2026-02-09T11:57:10.533Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-09T11:57:10.533Z","version":1},{"id":"mlf4aaklci2udp29ymo","type":"text","x":790,"y":2990,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","text":"How target sync works\n\nServer-side: when SubmitProjectResultsV3 is called\nfor a rule with migration_id:\n\n1. Check if MigrationTarget already exists\n   (match by migration_id + repo + path_in_repo)\n2. If not exists → create new target\n3. If exists + still has violations → keep NOT_STARTED\n4. If exists + now passes → update to DONE\n5. Enrich ownership_tag via DevEx API(artifactId)\n6. Enrich framework from Falcon PackageInfo\n\nResult: Standards check = automatic target discovery\nEvery CI build syncs targets for migration-linked rules","fontSize":14,"fontFamily":"5","createdAt":"2026-02-09T11:57:10.533Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-09T11:57:10.533Z","version":1}]}
