ed + code fixed:\n  → rule.check() returns pass\n  → ProjectReport: passing[]\n  → MigrationTarget → DONE\n\nPR merged but still broken:\n  → rule.check() returns violations\n  → target stays NOT_STARTED\n  → can retry with new run","fontSize":14,"fontFamily":"5","createdAt":"2026-02-09T11:57:47.863Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-09T11:57:47.863Z","version":1},{"id":"mlf4b3dgmsd474mr2hk","type":"rectangle","x":650,"y":3760,"width":620,"height":210,"backgroundColor":"#fff9db","strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","createdAt":"2026-02-09T11:57:47.863Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-09T11:57:47.863Z","version":1},{"id":"mlf4b3dg1eju66o72sa","type":"text","x":660,"y":3770,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","text":"What Standards provides for free\n\nBy linking Migration to Rule, you get ALL Standards features automatically:\n  • Enforcement: BREAK_BUILD or BLOCK_ROLLOUT\n  • Grace periods: milestones with start/end dates\n  • Opt-outs: teams can request extensions, commitments, emergencies\n  • Regression tracking: detect when fixed projects break again\n  • Dashboard visibility: all migration progress in Standards dashboard\n  • Robocop alerts: Slack notifications for regressions\n  • BI reporting: daily metrics on migration adoption\n\nNo need to rebuild any of this in the migration system!","fontSize":14,"fontFamily":"5","createdAt":"2026-02-09T11:57:47.863Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-09T11:57:47.863Z","version":1}],"count":10}
