 progress","fontSize":20,"createdAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","version":1},{"id":"mlgq29ebmh9ft6ezr8","type":"text","x":3000,"y":830,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","text":"EXAMPLE: React Class → Hooks Migration","fontSize":24,"createdAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","version":1},{"id":"mlgq29ebojmd3ky3q5","type":"rectangle","x":3000,"y":870,"width":950,"height":250,"backgroundColor":"transparent","strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"createdAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","version":1},{"id":"mlgq29ebytw4elfljcn","type":"text","x":3015,"y":880,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","text":"1. Setup: Migration(logical_id: 'react-hooks', deterministic: false)\n   Link to rule 'react-class-to-hooks' via migration_id\n   MigrationPrompt with system/user instructions for conversion\n\n2. CI Check: Developer pushes to 'my-app', Standards check runs\n   Rule finds 3 class components → violations[LoginForm, UserProfile, Dashboard]\n\n3. Auto-Target: rule has migration_id → create MigrationTarget\n   repo: 'wix/my-app', path: 'src/components', framework: NODE, owner: 'my-team'","fontSize":20,"createdAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","version":1},{"id":"mlgq29ebkgge95nrv","type":"rectangle","x":3000,"y":1140,"width":950,"height":225,"backgroundColor":"transparent","strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"createdAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","version":1},{"id":"mlgq29eb4smlzlwdqpu","type":"text","x":3015,"y":1150,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","text":"4. Fix: auto_autofix_enabled → Astra creates MigrationRun\n   deterministic: false → AI agent with prompt runs\n   Agent transforms class components to hooks, creates PR #1234\n   MigrationCheck: BUILD ✓ TEST ✓ LINT ✓\n\n5. Feedback: AutofixResult.pr_number=1234, status=SUCCESS\n   Target: PR_CREATED → review → MERGED → DONE\n   Standards dashboard shows migration progress across all artifacts","fontSize":20,"createdAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","version":1},{"id":"mlgq29eb0ltv1vb79hla","type":"rectangle","x":3000,"y":1420,"width":950,"height":175,"backgroundColor":"transparent","strokeColor":"#1971c2","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"createdAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","version":1},{"id":"mlgq29eb1xxn9c7b114","type":"text","x":3015,"y":1430,"strokeColor":"#1971c2","text":"KEY PRINCIPLE: One system, two modes\n───────────────────────────────────────────\nMigration with deterministic=true → replaces old rule.fix() completely\nMigration with deterministic=false → AI agent with prompt\nBoth tracked through same MigrationRun pipeline with full audit\nStandards provides for FREE: enforcement, grace periods, opt-outs, dashboards","fontSize":20,"createdAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","updatedAt":"2026-02-10T14:54:33.491Z","version":1}]}
